videos.headline: Washington State's opening return TD called back
videos.description: Washington State's Renard Bell returns the kickoff to the house, but it is called back for a hold against Washington State to the 10-yard line.

videos.headline: Washington State's Falk intercepted on first drive
videos.description: Washington State QB Luke Falk is intercepted by California's Camryn Bynum at the Washington State 20-yard line.

videos.headline: Cougars turn the ball over for second time in first  quarter
videos.description: Cal's Jaylinn Hawkins punches the ball loose from Jamire Calvin, Cal recovers the fumble.

videos.headline: Enwere bulldozes his way into the end zone
videos.description: Cal's Vic Enwere powers through multiple defenders on way to 6-yard touchdown run.

videos.headline: Bynum snags second INT of the night
videos.description: Cal's Camryn Bynum intercepts Luke Falk's pass in the end zone for his second interception in the first half.

videos.headline: Washington State's punter shanks punt
videos.description: Washington State punter Mitchell Cox sends punt just one yard, setting up Cal in Cougar territory with under a minute left in the first half.

videos.headline: Wells catches TD as time expires in the first half
videos.description: Cal's Ross Bowers completes play-action pass to Kyle Wells for a touchdown to increase Cal's lead at halftime.

videos.headline: Wilcox: 'Turnovers have been key for us'
videos.description: Cal coach Justin Wilcox talks about how important the last-second touchdown was and how the Cal defense needs to keep attacking the ball.

videos.headline: Washington State in trouble against Cal
videos.description: California forcing two interceptions and Ross Bowers throwing for 159 yards and a touchdown has No. 8 Washington State down at the half.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Washington State-Cal Halftime) 2017/10/13 ESHEET ENHL

videos.headline: Falk throws third INT of the night
videos.description: Cal's Raymond Davidson III intercepts Luke Falk's deflected pass for the Golden Bears' fourth forced turnover of the game.

videos.headline: Falk throws his fourth INT
videos.description: Luke Falk throws behind his receiver, the ball is tipped in to the hands of Jordan Kunaszyk for Falk's fourth INT of the night and Washington State's fifth turnover.

videos.headline: Rockett ejected for targeting
videos.description: Cal's Matt Rockett gets ejected after being penalized for targeting on the kickoff following a Golden Bears field goal.

videos.headline: Bowers front flips over defender into the end zone
videos.description: Cal's Ross Bowers runs 7 yards and flips into the end zone for the "jaw dropping" touchdown.

videos.headline: Falk is strip sacked for scoop and score by the Golden Bears
videos.description: Cal's Jordan Kunaszyk strip sacks Luke Falk, Gerran Brown picks up the fumble and takes it 26 yards for the touchdown.

videos.headline: Falk throws fifth INT after ball is tipped numerous times
videos.description: Washington State's Luke Falk has his pass deflected off several players and eventually intercepted for the Cougars' seventh turnover of the night.

videos.headline: Wilcox 'really proud' of his team after upsetting No. 8 Washington State
videos.description: Cal coach Justin Wilcox talks about how the Golden Bears were able to upset Washington State 37-3.

videos.headline: Bowers: 'we're onto the next week'
videos.description: Cal QB Ross Bowers says it's a great win but we have to be ready to go next week.

videos.headline: Cal pulls off the 'stunner' of Washington State
videos.description: Adam Amin and Dusty Dvoracek break down Cal's dominant upset victory over No. 8 Washington State.

videos.headline: No. 8 Washington State dominated by Cal
videos.description: Cougars' Luke Falk throws five interceptions and Golden Bears' Ross Bowers scores his first career touchdown on the ground, along with a score and 259 yards in the air, sending Washington State to the stunning 37-3 loss.

videos.headline: Cal has a field day with 7 turnovers
videos.description: The Golden Bears' defense has a perfect game against the Cougars as they force five interceptions and two fumble recoveries, one of which results in a touchdown.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Cal has a field day with 7 turnovers) 2017/10/13 ESHEET
